-- Basic Element to Invest $330 Million to Triple Grain Trading
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-05-14T14:59:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/basic-element-to-invest-330-million-to-triple-grain-trading.html
Billionaire Oleg Deripaska’s Basic
Element plans to spend more than 10 billion rubles ($330
million) to triple grain sales to 1.5 million metric tons by
2016, Andrey Oleynik, the company’s managing director for
agricultural business, told reporters in Moscow today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
